HOUSE BILL NO. HB0217
Random hand count audits of election results.
Sponsored by: Representative(s) Lucas, Allemand, Bear,
Brady, Brown, G, Guggenmos, Heiner, Smith, S
and Webb and Senator(s) Pearson
A BILL
for
1 AN ACT relating to elections; requiring a hand count audit
2 of ballots as specified; requiring rulemaking; and
3 providing for an effective date.
4
5 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Wyoming:
6
7 Section 1. W.S. 22-6-130 by creating a new subsection
8 (c) is amended to read:
9
10 22-6-130. Post-election ballot audit.
11
12 (c) In addition to the audit under subsections (a)
13 and (b) of this section, following each primary and general
14 election, each county clerk shall conduct an audit of the
15 ballots in one (1) precinct as provided in this section.
1 HB0217

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0673
1 The secretary of state shall randomly select one (1)
2 precinct in each county to be audited as provided in this
3 subsection. The county clerk shall conduct a hand count
4 audit of all ballots cast in the precinct selected by the
5 secretary of state and shall compare the hand count result
6 to the result tabulated by the electronic voting system.
7 The audit under this subsection shall be completed not
8 later than one (1) week after the date of the election. The
9 results of the audit and the comparison shall immediately
10 be reported to the secretary of state. The secretary of
11 state shall adopt rules necessary to implement this
12 subsection, including rules establishing the scope of the
13 audit and the procedures for conducting the audit under
14 this subsection.
15
16 Section 2. The secretary of state shall adopt rules
17 regarding the hand count audit required under W.S.
18 22-6-130(c), as created by section 1 of this act, not later
19 than September 1, 2025.
